Privacy Policy
Effective Date: [2024/9/18]
We, at
Screen Recorder-Video maker
("we," "our," or "the App"), are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information when you use our application, in accordance with applicable laws, including the
General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
and
Google Play Developer Policies
. We advise you to read this document thoroughly to understand how your personal data will be handled.
1. Information We Collect
We collect several types of information to enhance your experience and provide our services efficiently. The categories of data we may collect include:
1.1 Device Information
When you use our app, we may automatically collect information about the device you are using. This may include:
Device model
Operating system version
Unique device identifiers (e.g., IMEI, UUID)
Network information (e.g., Wi-Fi, mobile network)
Browser type and version
1.2 Log Information
We automatically log information related to your usage of the app. This includes:
Time and date of access
Duration of app usage
Features accessed
App crashes and diagnostic reports
1.3 Location Data
With your explicit permission, we may collect precise or approximate location information. This data helps us provide location-based services, such as tagging documents with location metadata.
1.4 User-Provided Information
You may provide personal information directly to us through various means, such as:
Contact information (e.g., email address)
Scanned documents and images uploaded via the app
Feedback, inquiries, or support requests
Information shared during registration for an account (if applicable)
1.5 Document Metadata
When you scan documents, metadata related to the document such as the file name, file type, and document size may be collected to facilitate file management.
1.6 Cookies and Tracking Technologies
Our app may use cookies or similar tracking technologies to enhance user experience and track user interactions. We may collect cookie data for session management, authentication, and personalization of services.
1.7 Payment Information
If you opt for premium services, we may collect payment-related information through third-party payment processors. This may include:
Billing address
Payment method details (e.g., credit card number)
Please note that we do not store payment information directly. Instead, we rely on secure third-party payment processors that are GDPR-compliant.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to provide and improve our services, personalize your experience, and ensure compliance with legal requirements. The primary purposes include:
2.1 Providing Services
Allowing you to scan, convert, and manage documents
Enabling cloud storage integrations, document sharing, and PDF creation
Accessing location data for location-based tagging and categorization of documents
2.2 Improving User Experience
We use the data we collect to:
Personalize the app interface and experience based on your preferences
Analyze user behavior and feature interaction to improve the app’s performance and user satisfaction
Enhance the design and functionality of future updates
2.3 Customer Support
Responding to your requests for assistance and support
Managing feedback and suggestions for product development
2.4 Security and Fraud Prevention
We use device and log information to detect and prevent fraud, unauthorized access, and abuse of our services. This ensures:
The safety and integrity of your data and documents
Compliance with Google Play’s Developer Policies regarding secure data processing
2.5 Legal Compliance
We may use your information to comply with applicable legal obligations, such as:
Protecting our rights, privacy, safety, or property and that of our users
Enforcing the terms of use and agreements related to our app
3. Sharing of Information
We understand the importance of keeping your personal data confidential. However, in certain circumstances, we may share your data with third parties as outlined below:
3.1 Service Providers
We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers to facilitate app functionality. These providers assist in:
Cloud storage (e.g., Google Drive, Dropbox)
Payment processing
Analytics and user behavior tracking
Customer support platforms
All service providers are contractually obligated to protect your data and comply with GDPR and other applicable regulations.
3.2 Legal Compliance
We may disclose your information when required by law, such as in response to a subpoena or a lawful government request. Additionally, we may share information to:
Investigate fraud, security breaches, or abuse of our app
Enforce our legal agreements or policies
Protect our rights and the rights of our users
3.3 Business Transfers
If we undergo a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your personal information may be transferred as part of that transaction. In such cases, we will notify you before your personal information becomes subject to a different privacy policy.
3.4 With Your Consent
We will share your personal information with third parties when you have given us explicit consent to do so.
4. Data Retention
We will retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which we collected it, including complying with legal, accounting, or reporting obligations. Retention periods vary depending on the type of data:
Scanned documents
: Retained until you delete them from the app
Log information
: Retained for diagnostic and analytics purposes
Account information
: Retained as long as your account remains active or as required by law
5. Your Rights and Choices
As a user in the
European Union (EU)
or under the
General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
, you have several important rights with respect to your personal information:
5.1 Access
You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you.
5.2 Correction
You can request that we correct any inaccurate or incomplete personal data.
5.3 Deletion
You have the right to request that we delete your personal data under certain conditions, such as when it is no longer necessary for the purposes for which it was collected or when you withdraw your consent.
5.4 Objection to Processing
You may object to the processing of your personal data, especially in cases of direct marketing.
5.5 Restriction of Processing
You may request that we restrict the processing of your personal data under specific circumstances, such as when you contest the accuracy of the data.
5.6 Data Portability
You have the right to request that your personal data be transferred to another service provider in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.
5.7 Withdrawal of Consent
You may withdraw your consent to our processing of your personal data at any time. This will not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at [Insert Contact Emai:developer@pdfreaderfreeview.com.
6. Data Security
We implement robust security measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. These measures include:
Encryption of sensitive data
Regular security assessments and audits
Secure authentication protocols for access control
Restricted access to authorized personnel only
However, no data transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
7. Children’s Privacy
Our services are not directed towards individuals under the age of 18, and we do not knowingly collect personal data from minors. If you are under 18, please do not provide us with any personal information. If we learn that we have collected personal data from a child under 18, we will take immediate steps to delete such information.
8. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your user experience, gather analytics, and serve targeted advertisements.
Cookies
are small text files placed on your device that help us track user preferences and activities. You have the option to manage your cookie preferences:
Accept all cookies
: For full access to app features and services
Reject non-essential cookies
: To block certain cookies related to marketing or analytics
For more information on how we use cookies, refer to our [Cookie Policy].
